<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1441,587,900]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,587,611]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus in the same clade with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1938" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1938" box="[758,1110,587,612]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Neoxeniades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[758,910,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Neoxeniades</emphasis>
Hayward, 1938
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1128,1182,588,612]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hayward, 1938" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Neoxeniades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="musarion">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Neoxeniades musarion</emphasis>
Hayward, 1938
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2019" authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[570,652,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Coolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[570,652,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Coolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[659,742,620,644]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and in a different subtribe (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[1088,1211,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carystina</taxonomicName>
) from 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1901]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vettius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1290,1376,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Vettius</emphasis>
Godman, [1901]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[350,404,652,676]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Cramer, [1777]" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1777" box="[501,877,651,676]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phyllus">
<emphasis box="[501,685,651,675]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Papilio phyllus</emphasis>
Cramer, [1777]
</taxonomicName>
), which is in Moncina (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1237,652,676]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="25.[192,275,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,215,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[192,1440,213,1561]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 10. Genomic trees of Erionotini, Carystina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677255/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Keys to J.45.21 and J.45.15b. Distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[679,827,684,708]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: uncus almost undivided, arms medium to short; gnathos small, narrow, about the same as uncus in lateral view; valva plate-like without processes, harpe about half of the valva, with a small notch on dorsal margin; no brands on forewing; mid tibiae smooth; milky-white areas on hindwing below, especially near the base, gradually turning brown towards outer margin; veins not darker. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly294.13.2:A968C, aly1249.14.7:A1222T, aly822.47.3:A218G, aly 
<date box="[228,336,876,900]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" value="1838-08-02">
<collectingDate box="[228,336,876,900]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" value="1838-08-02">1838.8.2</collectingDate>
</date>
:A172C, aly127.74.5: 
<specimenCode box="[585,650,875,899]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">T874</specimenCode>
C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1440,924,980]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,924,948]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, named both for the milky pattern on the hindwing below and to honor skipper taxonomist Olaf H. H. Mielke.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1440,1003,1060]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,434,1003,1027]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[500,553,1004,1028]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bell, 1941" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1941" box="[666,985,1003,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugi">
<emphasis box="[666,847,1003,1027]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Carystus klugi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bell" box="[857,985,1004,1028]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref26637" refString="Bell, E. L. 1941. New species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1125: 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1941">Bell, 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, [1824]" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1824" box="[999,1435,1003,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucretius">
<emphasis box="[999,1223,1003,1027]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Hesperia lucretius</emphasis>
Latreille, [1824]
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1886" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1886" box="[246,580,1035,1060]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diana">
<emphasis box="[246,433,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Hesperia diana</emphasis>
Plötz, 1886
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,796,1084,1108]" box="[192,796,1084,1108]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,1084,1108]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Mabille 1878" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[501,793,1084,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carystina Mabille 1878</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
